06_01 - Working with built-in Genesis SEO options	
	- SEO Settings will now show in Genesis if you have another SEO plugin activated
	- if a new page/post is added, Theme SEO Settings can be set - https://www.screencast.com/t/MfTKlYdXOfLy
	- Custom SEO configuration - check genesis SEO documentation (StudioPress account) - https://www.screencast.com/t/B2FvabbKUq
	
06_02 - Using the Genesis Import Export feature
	- the exported json won't include post/pages/images, it is only the genesis settings that will be saved to another site.
	  https://www.screencast.com/t/zJWUi0pibEb8

06_03 - Working with Genesis templates
    - Archive template is a quick way for creating a sitemap - https://www.screencast.com/t/hS45yEJbmPb9
